{"lemma":"سَكَبِ","slug":"سَكَبِ","root":"س.ك.ب","root_slug":"س-ك-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20176","n20177","n20178"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pour, to spill","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَكَبَ (sakaba).","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spilling, pouring, pouring out","tags":["uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of سَكَبَ (sakaba)."},"ipa":["/sa.ka.ba/","/sakb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20176","headword_ar":"سَكَبَ","root":"skb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwbN","text_ar":"سُكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakobN","text_ar":"سَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasokaAbN","text_ar":"تَسْكَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, [this last assigned in the K to the trans. verb,]) said of water, (S, A, Msb, K,) and a flow of tears ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoE","text_ar":"دَمْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (A, TA,) and the like, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It poured out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, poured out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anskb","text_ar":"انسكب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakabahu","text_ar":"سَكَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) aor. as above, (A, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakobN","text_ar":"سَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasokaAbN","text_ar":"تَسْكَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, [the latter assigned in the S to the intrans. verb,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He poured it out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, water, (S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) and a flow of tears, (A, TA,) and the like; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Askbhu","text_ar":"اسكبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) The people of El-Medeeneh say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ausokubo EalaY","text_ar":"اُسْكُبْ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yad aY~a","text_ar":"يَد َىَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pour thou out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, upon my hands."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAhunaA tusokabu AlEabaraAtu","text_ar":"هَاهُنَا تُسْكَبُ العَبَرَاتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Here tears are to be poured forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning this is the place in which one should weep, seeking forgiveness. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","TA","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n20177","headword_ar":"سَكْبٌ","root":"skb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkibN","text_ar":"سَاكِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakuwbN","text_ar":"سَكُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayokabN","text_ar":"سَيْكَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakiybN","text_ar":"سَكِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK [omitted in the TA and in my MS. copy of the K]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usokuwbN","text_ar":"اُسْكُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) Water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being poured out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running upon the surface of the earth without any excavation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the first signifies water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"poured out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is an inf. n. used as an epithet, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sab~N","text_ar":"صَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaworN","text_ar":"غَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied as epithets to water: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakuwbN","text_ar":"سَكُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running upon the surface of the earth without any excavation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usokuwbN","text_ar":"اُسْكُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", water"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being poured out"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har pp. 469 et seq.:) and also this last,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"running"},{"kind":"text","text":"water: (TA:) or this signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^imu AlhaTalaAni","text_ar":"دَايِمُ الهَطَلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continually pouring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continually pouring dispersedly and in large drops;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakobN","text_ar":"سَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for hence it appears evident that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlhaTalaAnu Ald~aAy^imu","text_ar":"الهَطَلَانُ الدَّايِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~akobu","text_ar":"السَّكْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^usokuwbu","text_ar":"الاُسْكُوبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~aAy^imu AlhaTalaAni","text_ar":"الدَّايِمُ الهَطَلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and is applied as an epithet to water and to blood; (A;) and also [probably in this sense] to clouds ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"); and to a wound made with a spear or the like ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEonapN","text_ar":"طَعْنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAkibN","text_ar":"سَاكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied as an epithet to tears ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"damoEN","text_ar":"دَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakobN","text_ar":"سَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a horse means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wide in step:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent in running;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that runs much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usokuwbN","text_ar":"اُسْكُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", so applied, has one or another of these meanings: (A:) or the former, thus applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that runs vehemently;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoDN","text_ar":"فَيْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; likened to water pouring forth: (EthThaalebee, TA:) also, (K, TA,) applied to a horse and a man and a boy, (TA,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of spirit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brisk, lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sprightly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~akobu","text_ar":"السَّكْبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was the name of the first horse possessed by the Prophet; (Mgh, * K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~akabu","text_ar":"السَّكَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the name of a horse of Shebeeb Ibn-Mo'áwiyeh. (K.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain sort of clothes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thin so as to resemble dust, and as though resembling pouring water by reason of its thinness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so, accord. to IAar, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakabN","text_ar":"سَكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, TA.) ―         -b4-  Applied to a man, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saqobN","text_ar":"سَقْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"necessary"},{"kind":"text","text":"thing or affair: (A, K, TA:) and (tropical:)  a disgrace ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sub~apN","text_ar":"سُبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"necessary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unavoidable."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) Lakeet Ibn-Zurárah said to his brother Maabad, when he required him to ransom him with two hundred camels, he being a captive,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"numiyTu Eanoka $ayoy^FA yakuwnu EalaY A^aholi bayotika sub~apF sakobFA","text_ar":"نُمِيطُ عَنْكَ شَيْيًا يَكُونُ عَلَى اَهْلِ بَيْتِكَ سُبَّةً سَكْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We will put away from thee a thing that would be to the people of thy house"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a necessary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unavoidable, disgrace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Copper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brass;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nuHaAsN","text_ar":"نُحَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lead:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakabN","text_ar":"سَكَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) in the latter sense, or in both senses, or in all the senses. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","A","Mgh","T","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n20178","headword_ar":"سَكَبٌ","root":"skb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, latter half, in three places.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sweet odour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though its odour were that of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the perfume called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaluwq","text_ar":"خَلُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing apart from others, upon a single root, having a downy substance, and leaves like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaEotar","text_ar":"صَعْتَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of origanum,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marjoram"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"except in being more green: it grows in the plains and the valleys; and what has dried up thereof is of no use to any one: it has a fruit which is eaten, and the people of El-Hijáz make of it a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beverage such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy*","text_ar":"نَبِيذ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its fruit does not grow forth in one year, but only in several years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"AHn says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakab","text_ar":"سَكَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a herb that rises to the height of a cubit, having dustcoloured leaves like those of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hinodabaA='","text_ar":"هِنْدَبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"endive"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a blossom intensely white, of the form of that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firosik","text_ar":"فِرْسِك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peach,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"variety thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) As mentions the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakab","text_ar":"سَكَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the plants of the plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, tracts."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  It is also said to be The ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ryH","text_ar":"ريح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray~iH","text_ar":"رَيِّح"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyH","text_ar":"رِيح"},{"kind":"text","text":"which seem to be coll. gen. ns. of each of which the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ray~iHapN","text_ar":"رَيِّحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a yellow blossom."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anemone"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"شَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uEomaAni","text_ar":"النُّعْمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of the trees of the hot season."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}